caption: Nice little public garden, right in the middle of the Montparnasse area. While really pleasant in pandemic time, it is usually a bit noisy due to nearby boulevard Montparnasse. Tip: a drinking water fountain is available at the back.

It is a generally quiet park along the church except in good weather at midday: it is invaded by students/high school students who take advantage of it for a snack on a bench. There is a small play area for young children.

-A small urban park- It's a small park next to the church. It wasn't too big, so it was perfect for letting my 1 year and 5 month old play. Like any park, it's full of adults eating take-out lunches at noon on weekdays. In the evening, many sitters come with their children, so the number of children increases. There aren't many Asian kids here, but they don't mind playing with each other. There are also some play equipment.
Small neighborhood square, ideal for snacking on a midday snack. The pigeons are there! Not very maintained and some renovations would be nice! Regularly squat at night!
Square Pleasant & shaded with flowers, with lots of seats and games for young children. Perfect for catching your breath in peace.
Presence of rats as in many Parisian squares. Mass cannabis consumers in plain sight. Proper maintenance of green spaces.
Small square, a little secluded, clean, quiet, trash cans available, nice for a bite to eat or a break in the shade
I won't say a park, I would rather say a garden in which we were able to sit on a bench near the church quietly and chat.
Small public garden where I sat on a bench for about an hour while waiting to access a place. Calm, green and peaceful.
Pleasant park, there are many benches (not always very clean :/) and play structures for children
